The included program is a reduced testcase of an server where each request is represented with a javascript Promise. We create a rust future for each javascript promise and wait for them to complete. The waiting is done with FuturesUnordered, so only if wake() is called will the corresponding future be polled. The problem is that poll_event_loop doesn't guarantee that.

When running the program, it prints

```
espindola 29 0x55fbbf71a8a8 Pending
espindola 29 0x55fbbf669c68 Pending
espindola 29 0x55fbbf71a8a8 Pending
espindola 29 0x55fbbf71a8a8 Ready(Ok(()))
espindola 99
```

Which show that one of futures is polled until complete, but since wake() is not called for the second, the program blocks waiting for the second one without ever calling poll in it.

```rust
