Currently `Deno.FileInfo` doesn't include FS path. The path is easily available to the "stat" functions and could be included. Lacking the path leads to wrapper functions and sometimes wrapper classes. This could be trivially fixed.

There are additional considerations like path normalization, file being moved after stat, and so on. But they're present in all FS operations. Other `FileInfo` fields can also get outdated. So I don't think those concerns are relevant.

---

Additional consideration: `Deno.FileInfo` would be more flexible if it were defined as a class, with `stat`/`statSync` converted to its static methods. In this case, the behavior could be more easily customized via subclassing. I ended up with the following. For example's sake, the definition is stripped down.

```js
class FileInfo {
  constructor(stat, path) {
    this.stat = reqStruct(stat)
    this.path = reqPath(path)
  }

  isFile() {return this.stat.isFile}
  isDir() {return this.stat.isDirectory}

  onlyFile() {return this.isFile() ? this : undefined}
  onlyDir() {return this.isDir() ? this : undefined}

  static async stat(path) {
    return new this(await Deno.stat(reqPath(path)), path)
  }
}
```

If `Deno.FileInfo` was originally defined as a class, then extending it with support for `.path` would have been simpler, without a wrapper layer:

```js
class FileInfo extends Deno.FileInfo {
  static async stat(path) {
    const out = await super.stat(path)
    out.path = path
    return out
  }
}
```

I think this flexibility is worth considering, but wouldn't spend much time arguing. Just throwing it out there.

If you open a WebSocketStream and do nothing but listen for messages, then you will have a fatal error after a minute.

Most public websocket test servers disconnect after a minute of inactivity which makes this issue hard to test with them, so first here's a script for running a test websocket server:

<details><summary>echoServer.ts</summary>

```typescript
// echoServer.ts
function wsHandler(ws: WebSocket) {
  ws.onopen = () => {};
  ws.onmessage = (event) => {
    console.log("message: " + event.data);
    ws.send("echo: " + event.data);
  };
  ws.onclose = () => {};
}

async function requestHandler(event: Deno.RequestEvent) {
  try {
    const pathname = new URL(event.request.url).pathname;
    if (event.request.method === "GET" && pathname === "/ws") {
      const { socket, response } = Deno.upgradeWebSocket(event.request);
      wsHandler(socket);
      event.respondWith(response);
    } else {
      event.respondWith(new Response("404 Not Found", { status: 404 }));
    }
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
    event.respondWith(
      new Response("500 Internal Server Error", { status: 500 })
    );
  }
}

const server = Deno.listen({ hostname: "localhost", port: 8080 });
for await (const conn of server) {
  (async () => {
    const httpConn = Deno.serveHttp(conn);
    for await (const requestEvent of httpConn) {
      requestHandler(requestEvent);
    }
  })();
}
```

