We added `.close` method, and deprecated `.return` method in #10577. While `.close` is fine as a way for users to explicitly close the watcher, there were some inputs from the community that `.return` method is also useful for automatically closing the watcher when you break from the async iterable loop. (Thanks @mitranim and @connorlogin for the suggestions)

```js
const watcher = Deno.watchFs(".");
for await (const event of watcher) {
  if (event.kind === "remove") {
    break;
  }
}
// Here you still need to call watcher.close(), if we removed `.return` in 2.0
```

So I suggest we should cancel the deprecation of `.return` and keep it as is (with the clarification of the purpose of each method.)

