`deno task` has a characteristic that if you execute a task anywhere in the directory tree it will use the deno.json's dir as the cwd. This is nice because you can define tasks that use relative paths and have the tasks work when you execute them from any directory.

Sometimes this is not nice though and for those situations there should be an opt-in way to set the cwd that a deno task uses when it starts up. For example, the following is not possible at the moment:

```jsonc
{
  "tasks": {
    // doesn't work, because `deno task wasmbuild` will start in this deno.json's directory
    "build:crypto": "cd _wasm_crypto && deno task wasmbuild",
    "build:hash": "cd hash/_wasm && deno task wasmbuild",
    "build:varint": "cd _wasm_varint && deno task wasmbuild",
    "wasmbuild": "deno run --unstable -A --no-check https://deno.land/x/wasmbuild@0.5.0/main.ts"
  }
}
```

Instead you need to do the following, which creates multiple sources of truth:

```jsonc
{
  "tasks": {
    "build:crypto": "cd _wasm_crypto && deno run --unstable -A --no-check https://deno.land/x/wasmbuild@0.5.0/main.ts",
    "build:hash": "cd hash/_wasm && deno run --unstable -A --no-check https://deno.land/x/wasmbuild@0.5.0/main.ts",
    "build:varint": "cd _wasm_varint && deno run --unstable -A --no-check https://deno.land/x/wasmbuild@0.5.0/main.ts"
  }
}
```

To fix this, it would be useful to have a way to set the cwd of a deno task. Probably a `--cwd <path>` option:

```jsonc
{
  "tasks": {
    "build:crypto": "deno task --cwd _wasm_crypto wasmbuild",
    "build:hash": "deno task --cwd hash/_wasm wasmbuild",
    "build:varint": "deno task --cwd _wasm_varint wasmbuild",
    "wasmbuild": "deno run --unstable -A --no-check https://deno.land/x/wasmbuild@0.5.0/main.ts"
  }
}
```

People could also do stuff like `deno task --cwd . wasmbuild` in order to use the cwd as the starting point of a deno task.

Ref: https://github.com/denoland/deno_std/pull/2319#discussion_r892434783

