As can be seen in the outputs:

- Deno does not serialize the non-enumerable property `foo` when using `{ showHiden: true }`

- Node.js does — although I think it's odd that it prints the property name surrounded by brackets because — in source code — that indicates a [computed property name](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Object_initializer#computed_property_names), so it suggests that `foo` is a variable and not a string

This seems like a bug to me.

